                          CLIFF:
                      All right!

08:02.415 --> 08:03.949
 We have a lot of Chinese food  
      delivered to Gary's.      

08:04.017 --> 08:05.117
                        Yeah?   

08:05.185 --> 08:07.519
        And not Moo Shu,        
  just the stuff no one likes.  

08:10.390 --> 08:11.790
    Yeah?                       

08:11.858 --> 08:15.160
Well, and then, you know,       
have to pay for it and stuff.   

08:15.228 --> 08:17.596
                    Sammy...    

08:17.664 --> 08:19.431
What?                           
         Look, we gotta think of
          something really good.

08:19.499 --> 08:20.466
                        NORM:   
                          Right.

08:20.533 --> 08:22.401
I mean, just for once,          
I'd like to be                  

08:22.469 --> 08:24.136
on the winning end              
of a great scam.                

08:24.204 --> 08:25.170
                          CLIFF:
                    Well, uh,   

08:25.238 --> 08:26.372
    just in case,               
    this morning,               

08:26.439 --> 08:28.073
         I happened             
to put on my Speedos.           

08:28.141 --> 08:29.241
  Cliff...                      

08:29.309 --> 08:30.242
No, no, no, no...               

08:31.745 --> 08:34.179
          Hey, Malone,          

08:34.246 --> 08:35.681
I'd like to talk                
to you for a second.            

08:35.749 --> 08:37.082
     (all groaning, booing)     

08:37.150 --> 08:40.785
      Hey, and I'm really,      
really sorry about this jukebox.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.654
That was the vintage one,       
        wasn't it?              

08:42.722 --> 08:43.889
                     Here. Um...

08:43.957 --> 08:46.291
    Oh, I feel awful.           
Let me make it up to you.       

08:46.359 --> 08:48.727
    (through nozzle):           
        ¶ Do it with me,        
        do it with me! ¶        

08:48.795 --> 08:49.995
      (horn solo blaring)       

08:50.063 --> 08:52.398
     ¶ Come on, Come on! ¶      

08:52.465 --> 08:53.999
     ¶ Do the vampire... ¶      

08:54.067 --> 08:57.002
  ¶ Do the vampire twist... ¶   

08:57.070 --> 08:58.470
          (song stops)          

08:58.538 --> 08:59.538
    You're good.                

08:59.673 --> 09:01.607
                    Yes, I know.

09:01.675 --> 09:03.709
          Here, I'd like to give
              you a blank check.

09:03.777 --> 09:05.611
        Whatever the damages,   
            just write it in.   

09:05.679 --> 09:06.945
            And I'd also like   

09:07.013 --> 09:08.647
             to call off all the
             pranks for tonight.

09:08.748 --> 09:09.882
What's going on here?           

09:09.949 --> 09:11.684
                 Well, I went to
                my doctor today.

09:11.751 --> 09:13.786
    He says I have abnormally   
            high blood pressure.

09:13.853 --> 09:15.354
                I'm 225 over 90.

09:15.422 --> 09:17.623
              Yeah, he also said
                if I don't start
                  taking it easy

09:17.691 --> 09:20.526
            soon, I could end up
        a lot worse, so you see,

09:20.627 --> 09:22.661
that's why we got to call off   
         everything for tonight.

09:22.729 --> 09:24.963
So this is not one              
of your pranks?                 

09:25.031 --> 09:27.032
    No, no, no, no-- Sam, I'm   
        on the level here, okay?

09:27.133 --> 09:28.367
        I'm really sorry        
    about everything, guys.     

09:28.435 --> 09:30.069
        A round of beers        
          on me, okay?          

09:30.136 --> 09:32.171
              Just add it to the
          check, Sam, all right?

09:32.238 --> 09:33.339
                          CLIFF:
                Thanks, Gary.   

09:33.406 --> 09:34.740
Oh, what are you talking about? 

09:34.808 --> 09:35.908
     Hey, come on, listen.      

09:35.975 --> 09:37.209
         Your health's          
      a lot more important      

09:37.277 --> 09:38.544
 than a bunch of silly pranks.  

09:38.611 --> 09:41.714
Wow, you're really              
a great guy, Sam.               

09:41.781 --> 09:43.148
Look, I got to go.              

09:43.283 --> 09:45.317
My wife's waiting               
in the car for me.              

09:45.385 --> 09:47.319
She's gonna take me home.       

09:49.456 --> 09:52.257
                Oh, are we going
              after him tonight!

09:53.226 --> 09:55.160
(laughing)                      

09:57.564 --> 10:00.232
            Sam, he just told   
                  you he's sick.

10:00.333 --> 10:01.633
        (laughing)              

10:01.701 --> 10:03.369
    She fell for that!          

10:03.436 --> 10:04.937
(mocking tone):                 
High blood pressure.            

10:05.005 --> 10:06.672
My wife's in the car            
waiting for me.                 

10:06.740 --> 10:09.108
Honey, don't you see what       
he's trying to do?              

10:09.175 --> 10:10.242
He's getting me                 
to lower my guard.              

10:10.310 --> 10:11.477
Oh, this is good,               
this is good.                   

10:11.578 --> 10:13.245
All we got to figure out now is,

10:13.313 --> 10:14.780
  is something that'll really   
    spook him tonight.          

10:14.848 --> 10:15.848
                          CLIFF:
                        Yeah.   
                        Yeah.   

10:15.915 --> 10:17.182
                        NORM:   
                        Yeah.   

10:17.250 --> 10:19.551
      Well, Sam, how about using
        the old bloody thumb?   

10:19.619 --> 10:20.953
            That's pretty scary.

10:21.021 --> 10:23.055
Come on, man,                   
forget the old bloody thumb.    

10:23.123 --> 10:24.556
    No chump would              
    fall for that.              

10:24.624 --> 10:26.925
            (register rings)    
Oh, gee!                        

10:26.993 --> 10:29.294
              Helps to have     
             the right chump.   

10:30.964 --> 10:32.031
             Maybe you gentlemen
              should be thinking

10:32.098 --> 10:33.165
                 along the lines
                of high-tech.   

10:33.233 --> 10:34.233
    What do you mean?           

10:34.334 --> 10:35.934
            Well, a hologram.   

10:36.002 --> 10:37.269
You project                     
a three-dimensional             

10:37.370 --> 10:39.238
            translucent image of
        some ghoulish apparition

10:39.339 --> 10:41.273
              right into Gary's,

10:41.341 --> 10:43.108
             thereby scaring the
            bejeezus out of 'em.

10:43.209 --> 10:44.176
                     Where'd you
                  get that idea?

10:44.310 --> 10:45.644
                 Well, actually,

10:45.712 --> 10:47.913
  Lilith and her physics friends
      pulled it on me last year.

10:47.981 --> 10:50.749
        Geez, I must have pulled
      out five fistfuls of hair.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.151
Hee, hee, hee...                

10:53.420 --> 10:55.587
    So, uh, what do you say,    
    guys, a hologram?           

10:55.655 --> 10:56.755
FRASIER:                        
Yeah.                           
        Yeah.                   
                        Yeah.   

10:56.823 --> 10:57.956
        ALL (chanting):         
      Hologram! Hologram!       

10:58.024 --> 11:00.025
 Hologram! Hologram! Hologram!  

11:05.732 --> 11:07.266
        Trick or treat,         
        everyone.               

11:09.235 --> 11:10.936
            Well, rather than   
                 let Freddy have

11:11.037 --> 11:13.472
         all the fun, we decided
         to get dressed up, too.

11:13.573 --> 11:15.207
                Who are you guys
                 supposed to be?

11:15.275 --> 11:17.209
See, Frasier, I told you        
they wouldn't know.             

11:19.079 --> 11:22.448
                 Well, I'm Dante
            Gabriel Rossetti!   

11:24.117 --> 11:26.618
And I'm his sister,             
Christina.                      

11:28.455 --> 11:30.422
The Rossettis are               
our favorite figures            

11:30.490 --> 11:32.358
from the Pre-Raphaelite         
Brotherhood.                    

